Ging's, a well-known theatrical costumier and fancy dress suppliers on Dame Street in Dublin. The closed down shop of Maurice Abrahams, Master Bespoke Tailor, is festooned with posters for Zero's Disco which also adorned our <a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/nlireland/6536658801/" target="_blank"><b>Upper Ormond Quay pissoir</b></a> in another Michael S. Walker photo from 1973. Thanks to <b><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/73371644@N04/" target="_blank">Slow Loose Chippings</a></b> for letting us know that &quot;<i>Zero's Disco was in Wolfe Tone St. &quot;Brush&quot; Sheils used to play there, amongst others!</i>&quot;

Here's the current <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?q=dame+street,+dublin,+ireland&amp;hl=en&amp;ll=53.344159,-6.26667&amp;spn=0.01085,0.028539&amp;sll=37.0625,-95.677068&amp;sspn=58.076329,116.894531&amp;hnear=Dame+St,+Dublin,+County+Dublin+City,+Ireland&amp;t=m&amp;z=16&amp;layer=c&amp;cbll=53.344156,-6.266815&amp;panoid=EsY_3azT_5PRLszfp0Qxtg&amp;cbp=12,147.94,,0,5.44" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><b>Street View</b></a>.

Thanks to <b>Niall McAuley</b> for a gorgeous photo of this location, including Ging's (from <b><a href="http://www.dublin.ie/forums/attachment.php?s=94b7d40ab312d5c889252071a882affb&amp;attachmentid=86165&amp;d=1320227483" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">dublin dot ie forums</a></b>).

<b>lkatadmirer</b> said that &quot;<i>Maurice Abrahams is now located in South Anne Street. The business is run by Mr Abrahams's son Declan and it is one of the best mens shops in Dublin.</i>&quot;

And very special thanks to <b>decospiper</b> for this lovely information:
&quot;<i>Katie Abrahams who is Declans daughter and Maurice's grandaughter found this photo today of our first 'proper retail' shop(very first shop was in Mary Street in 1962)The photo was taken when a compulsory purchase order by the council meant the whole block was to be knocked down to make way for the forecourt we now know beside Dublin Castle.And so,we progressed to 11 Parliament Street where we traded for about 20 years also opening our flagship Sth Anne Street shop where we still trade.Thanks to everyone here for finding this great photo for us!</i>&quot;

Date: 1973

